Package org.openlca.ipc

Class RpcRequest

java.lang.Object
org.openlca.ipc.RpcRequest
public class RpcRequest extends Object
A rpc call is represented by sending a Request object to a Server. See: http://www.jsonrpc.org/specification

  • Field Details

    • jsonrpc

      public String jsonrpc
      A String specifying the version of the JSON-RPC protocol. MUST be exactly "2.0".

    • method

      public String method
      A String containing the name of the method to be invoked. Method names that begin with the word rpc followed by a period character (U+002E or ASCII 46) are reserved for rpc-internal methods and extensions and MUST NOT be used for anything else.

    • params

      public com.google.gson.JsonElement params
      A Structured value that holds the parameter values to be used during the invocation of the method. This member MAY be omitted.

    • id

      public com.google.gson.JsonPrimitive id
      An identifier established by the Client that MUST contain a String, Number, or NULL value if included. If it is not included it is assumed to be a notification. The value SHOULD normally not be Null [1] and Numbers SHOULD NOT contain fractional parts
